<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0900 </DOCNO><TEXT>Lymphomas are primarily a malignancy of the lymph nodes. However, 18%- 25% of patients with non-Hodgkin lymphoma are first seen with diseaselocalized to a primary extraodal site. In an even greater percentagean extranodal site is involved as part of disseminated lymphoma. Thisexhibit illustrates the spectrum of CT and US findings of involvementby non-Hodgkin lymphoma at the less common extranodal sites. The prognosisand treatment by site are presented.</TEXT></DOC>